ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) — Patrick Gardner scored 22 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Marist controlled from the start beating Manhattan 61-50 on Tuesday night in an opening round contest of the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference tournament.After Marist’s early 12-4 lead, the Jaspers closed to 18-17 when Nick Brennen made a 3-pointer with 6:38 before halftime. But the Jaspers failed to score again, Marist (11-19) scored the next 18 points and went to halftime up 19. Gardner scored 10 in that span.Manhattan closed within four on two occasions — 48-44 and 50-46 — but never got closer.Ant Nelson scored 15 points and Josh Roberts 11 and grabbed 13 rebounds for Manhattan (12-18).___More AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and https://apnews.com/hub/ap-top-25-college-basketball-poll and https://twitter.com/AP_Top25